MLD Example (examples/ipv6/mld)
===================================

This example demonstrates IPv6 Multicast Listener Discovery using real
application-driven group membership. Two configurations are provided:

  MldDemo   - MLDv1 (RFC 2710), any-source multicast
  MldV2Ssm  - MLDv2 (RFC 3810), source-specific multicast (SSM)

Topology
--------
A shared Ethernet hub connects two listener hosts (host1, host2), one router
querier, and one UDP data sender. Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses.

Scenario (config MldDemo)
--------------------------
1. host1 and host2 join multicast group ff0e::1 by opening UdpSink sockets with
   multicastGroup="ff0e::1" — this fires an unsolicited Multicast Listener Report.
2. The Router6 querier sends a General Listener Query on the shared link every
   queryInterval seconds (first query at startupQueryInterval=2s).
3. host2 closes its UdpSink socket at stopTime=10s — this fires an MLD Done,
   which the router processes by sending a Multicast-Address-Specific Query for
   ff0e::1. host1 remains joined for the full simulation.
4. An optional UdpBasicApp sender transmits data to ff0e::1 to show delivery
   to the joined listeners.

Scenario (config MldV2Ssm)
--------------------------
Demonstrates source-specific multicast with MLDv2 (selected via
**.ipv6.mld.typename = "Mldv2"). Two sources, 'sender' (S1) and 'host2' (S2),
both transmit to the SSM group ff3e::8 (the FF3E::/32 range is reserved for SSM).
host1 subscribes to the group in INCLUDE mode naming only S1, so:
  - MLDv2 carries an INCLUDE{S1} membership (a State-Change Report with an
    ALLOW record naming S1's address), and
  - host1 receives S1's stream only; S2's packets to the same group are filtered
    out (host1 reports "received 10 packets", all from S1).

Run commands (from this directory)
----------------------------------
    inet -u Cmdenv -f omnetpp.ini -c MldDemo -r 0
    inet -u Cmdenv -f omnetpp.ini -c MldV2Ssm -r 0

Key EV markers to look for in the Cmdenv log (MldDemo)
------------------------------------------------------
    "sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 on iface="  (host join)
    "recorded listener for group=ff0e::1"                            (router records)
    "sending General Listener Query on iface="                       (router periodic query)
    "received General Listener Query on iface="                      (host sees query)
    "sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 on iface="    (host2 leave)
    "received Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1"             (router sees done)
    "sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1"     (router MAS query)
